        "title": "Adding file names to an array list in java",
        "body": "<p>I am currently needing to load the contents of a folders filenames to an arraylist I have but I am unsure as how to do this.<\/p>\n\n<p>To put it into perspective I have a folder with One.txt, Two.txt, Three.txt etc. I want to be able to load this list into an arraylist so that if I was to check the arraylist its contents would be :<\/p>\n\n<p>arraylist[0] = One <\/p>\n\n<p>arraylist[1] = Two<\/p>\n\n<p>arraylist[3] = Three<\/p>\n\n<p>If anyone could give me any insight into this it would be much appreciated. <\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 2532953,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "file"
        ],
