            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1269789331,
            "creation_date": 1269788356,
            "body": "<p>Here's a solution that uses <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/io/File.html#list%28java.io.FilenameFilter%29\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>java.io.File.list(FilenameFilter)<\/code><\/a>. It keeps the <code>.txt<\/code> suffix; you can strip these easily if you really need to.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>File dir = new File(\".\");\nList&lt;String&gt; list = Arrays.asList(dir.list(\n   new FilenameFilter() {\n      @Override public boolean accept(File dir, String name) {\n         return name.endsWith(\".txt\");\n      }\n   }\n));\nSystem.out.println(list);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 2533324,
            "question_id": 2532953,
            "last_edit_date": 1269789331
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2f364c2e36b52bc80296cbf23da8b231?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 9867,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 18393,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/18393/cletus",
                "reputation": 626980,
                "display_name": "cletus",
                "accept_rate": 82
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1269781559,
            "creation_date": 1269781559,
            "body": "<pre><code>File dir = new File(\"/some/path/name\");\nList&lt;String&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\nif (dir.isDirectory()) {\n  String[] files = dir.list();\n  Pattern p = Pattern.compile(\"^(.*?)\\\\.txt$\");\n  for (String file : files) {\n    Matcher m = p.matcher(file);\n    if (m.matches()) {\n      list.add(m.group(1));\n    }\n  }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 2532972,
            "question_id": 2532953
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d7d8f2d9904d869783dcff1803c6fbcb?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 41850,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 121747,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/121747/jack",
                "reputation": 133857,
                "display_name": "Jack",
                "accept_rate": 89
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1269781403,
            "creation_date": 1269781403,
            "body": "<p>You can try with<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>File folder = new File(\"myfolder\");\n\nif (folder.isDirectory())\n{\n  // you can get all the names\n  String[] fileNames = folder.list();\n\n  // you can get directly files objects\n  File[] files = folder.listFiles();\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 2532965,
            "question_id": 2532953
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/XXkyL.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 2113783,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1878494,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1878494/maarten",
                "reputation": 663,
                "display_name": "Maarten",
                "accept_rate": 41
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1365451098,
            "creation_date": 1365451098,
            "body": "<p>Here's My answer, I've used this before personally to get all the filenames,<br>\nto be used in a loadsave function in one of my games.<br><br><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>  public void getFiles(String path){\n            //Put filenames in arraylist&lt;string&gt;\n        File dir = new File(path);\n        ArrayList&lt;String&gt; filenames = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\n        for(File file : dir.listFiles()){\n            savefiles.add(file.getName());\n        }\n            //Check if the files are in the arraylist\n        for (int i = 0; i &lt; savefiles.size(); i++){\n            String s = savefiles.get(i);\n            System.out.println(\"File \"+i+\" : \"+s);\n        }\n        System.out.println(\"\\n\");\n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><br>I hope that may have been of use to you C: - Hugs rose<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 15887829,
            "question_id": 2532953
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/77302a6c0989999e15aebc7968310acb?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 113876,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 299713,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/299713/ziv",
                "reputation": 2441,
                "display_name": "Ziv",
                "accept_rate": 71
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1269781490,
            "creation_date": 1269781490,
            "body": "<p>See the Jave File API, particularly the <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.2/docs/api/java/io/File.html#list%28%29\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">list()<\/a> function. <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>File my_dir = new File(\"DirectoryName\");\nassert(my_dir.exists()); // the directory exists\nassert(my_dir.isDirectory()); // and is actually a directory\n\nString[] filenames_in_dir = my_dir.list();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Now <code>filenames_in_dir<\/code> is an array of all the filenames, which is almost precisely what you want.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you want to strip the extensions off the individual filenames, that's basic string handling - iterate over the filenames and take care of each one.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 2532969,
            "question_id": 2532953
        },
        {
            "owner": {
